http://news.gazeta.kz/art.asp?aid=352070


In Kyrgyzstan, an outbreak of foot and mouth disease
----------------------------------------------------
Questions of the epizootic situation in Kyrgyzstan were discussed at a
meeting in the government of the republic with the Acting Prime
Minister Omurbek Babanov, reports Kazinform.

The meeting heard information from the minister of agriculture
Torogula Bekov, General Director of State Veterinary Ministry of
Agriculture Zhanybek Sultanov. According to the minister of
agriculture, the FMD outbreak began 13 Sep 2011 in a village of the
Ak-Bashat Jaiyl area. At present, FMD is registered in cattle in vast
areas in Chui (Chuy), Issyk-Kul (Ysyk-Kol), Naryn and Jalal-Abad
regions.

During the last 10 months, vaccinations were applied in 2 313 634 head
of cattle, 1 239 800 sheep and goats and 1 073 800 goats.

However, despite the measures taken, in October the disease reemerged,
the causative agent being FMD virus type "A-Iran-5" which had not been
previously registered in the republic. Accordingly, no vaccine against
this type was purchased.

As a result of discussions, Omurbek Babanov instructed the Ministry of
Agriculture to take the strictest measures against those responsible
for the outbreak. In addition, he requested to contact relevant
research institutes for the purchase of vaccines against the
identified type of agent, and in general to develop a set of measures
for the prevention and control of communicable diseases in the
country.

"It is necessary to carry out systematic work on prevention and
control of various diseases in animals, and not to act every time only
after the start of an outbreak. All senior officials of the Veterinary
Services who have not acted to prevent the FMD infection, should
suffer severe punishment," summarized O. Babanov.

--
