[The last FMD outbreaks reported by Kyrgyzstan to the OIE date back to
May-July 2007, affecting cattle with serotypes A and O in the
provinces Batken and Chuy; the disease was, reportedly, continuing
during the 2nd semester of 2007 and the 1st semester of 2008. Since
mid-2007, no periodic reports from Kyrgyzstan have been submitted to
the OIE, though semiannual and annual reports are required from all
member counties.

In February 2010, press reports described an outbreak in the Naryn
province, apparently addressed by the veterinary service. No report
was submitted to the OIE and ProMED-mail's RFI received no response.

Such a lacune in epidemiological information from a central-Asian
country is a cause for concern to its neighbours and beyond. In a
world declared free of rinderpest, regular and reliable reporting has
become even more vital. - Mod.AS]
